      "content": "That's getting closer to the tone. It's a bit polite though. If they're actually worried about these activists fundamentally changing their town, they wouldn't just be talking about \"stirring up trouble\"—they'd be using more specific, colored language to describe these people and the \"nature\" of the problem. Can you push the dialogue further to reflect the more visceral, derogatory way they would actually refer to the activists and the perceived threat to their racial hierarchy? I want to see how they would use the language of the era to dehumanize them or justify their own actions.",
